<taxonomicName box="[670,763,1848,1874]" class="Maxillopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sessilia" pageId="1" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Sessilia</taxonomicName>
, the suborder Verrucomorpha was demonstrated to have had a scalpelliform ancestor, arising from this order via the Brachylepadomorpha 
<bibRefCitation author="Withers" box="[1137,1305,1888,1914]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Withers, T. H. (1923) Die Cirripedien der Kreide Rugens. Abhandlungen aus dem Geologisch-Palaontologischen Institut der Universitat zu Greifswald, 3, 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1923">
Withers, 
<number box="[1246,1305,1888,1914]" pageId="1" pageNumber="38" value="1923.0">1923</number>
</bibRefCitation>
during the Middle to Late Jurassic.
</paragraph>
